<p>Given an arrayÂ <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">nums</code>Â ofÂ <em>n</em>Â integers, are there elementsÂ <em>a</em>,Â <em>b</em>,Â <em>c</em>Â inÂ <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">nums</code>Â such thatÂ <em>a</em>Â +Â <em>b</em>Â +Â <em>c</em>Â = 0? Find all unique triplets in the array which gives the sum of zero.</p>

<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>

<p>The solution set must not contain duplicate triplets.</p>

<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Given array nums = [-1, 0, 1, 2, -1, -4],

A solution set is:
[
  [-1, 0, 1],
  [-1, -1, 2]
]
</code></pre></div></div>

